(5, '\r\nR-Programming', 'R is a dominant open-source programming language in the field of data analysis, statistics and data visualization. The ability to provide high-end support to statistical and graphical techniques such as linear/ nonlinear modelling, time-series analysis, clustering and many more, makes it highly extensible and popular amongst data analysts and data scientists. Used for statistical computing, R language helps in effective data manipulation across enterprises.', '<ul type=\"disc\"> <li>Instructor-led Classroom and Online</li> <li>Training modes</li> <li>Best-in-Class Training Curriculum</li> <li>Beginner to Expert Level Training</li> <li>Hands-on Programming Practice</li> <li>Pro-Python Tips & Tricks Practice Activities</li> <li>Unlimited Access - Online or Offline Flexible Guaranteed to Run Schedules</li> <li>Self-Paced Learning</li> </ul>', '<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li>Introduction to R and RStudio</li>\r\n<li>Business analytics foundation with R tools</li>\r\n<li>Introduction to Analytics</li>\r\n<li>Data structures: vectors, matrices, lists and data frames</li>\r\n<li>Reading data into R from various data sources</li>\r\n<li>Merging data across data sources\r\nStatistical concepts and their application in business</li>\r\n<li>Basic analytic techniques – Using R\r\nPredictive modelling techniques</li>\r\n<li>Statistical modelling functions: lm and glm</li>\r\n<li>Creating functions</li>\r\n<li>Iterating with R: logic and flow control</li>\r\n<li>Extending R with add-on packages and the R ecosystem</li>\r\n<li>Working with Graphics</li>\r\n</ul>', 'The R programming course is meant to best-fit the learning needs of individuals from statistical background and programmers. Familiarity with programming languages like Java or Python can be helpful, though not mandatory', 'R is a dominant open-source programming language in the field of data analysis, statistics and data visualization. The ability to provide high-end support to statistical and grap